### BrowserContext.addCookies

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/class-browsercontext.md

Adds cookies into the browser context. These cookies will be available to all pages within this context. The cookies parameter is an array of cookie objects, each with properties like name, value, url, domain, path, expires, httpOnly, secure, sameSite, and partitionKey.

```APIDOC
## POST /browserContext/addCookies

### Description
Adds cookies into this browser context. All pages within this context will have these cookies installed. Cookies can be obtained via `BrowserContext.cookies`.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/browserContext/addCookies

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **cookies** (Array<Object>) - Required - An array of cookie objects. Each object can have the following properties:
  - **name** (string) - Required - The name of the cookie.
  - **value** (string) - Required - The value of the cookie.
  - **url** (string) - Optional - Either `url` or both `domain` and `path` are required. For the cookie to apply to all subdomains as well, prefix domain with a dot, like this: ".example.com".
  - **domain** (string) - Optional - Either `url` or both `domain` and `path` are required. For the cookie to apply to all subdomains as well, prefix domain with a dot, like this: ".example.com".
  - **path** (string) - Optional - Either `url` or both `domain` and `path` are required.
  - **expires** (float) - Optional - Unix time in seconds.
  - **httpOnly** (boolean) - Optional.
  - **secure** (boolean) - Optional.
  - **sameSite** (("Strict"|"Lax"|"None")) - Optional.
  - **partitionKey** (string) - Optional - For partitioned third-party cookies (aka CHIPS), the partition key.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "cookies": [
    {
      "name": "cookie1",
      "value": "value1",
      "url": "https://example.com"
    },
    {
      "name": "cookie2",
      "value": "value2",
      "domain": ".example.com",
      "path": "/"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **None**

#### Response Example
```json
{}
```
```

