### Context Storage State Configuration

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/params.md

Populate browser context with storage state including cookies and local storage. Initialize contexts with previously saved authentication state and session data.

```APIDOC
## CONTEXT STORAGE STATE OPTION

### Description
Populates context with given storage state. Use this to initialize a context with logged-in information obtained via `BrowserContext.storageState` method.

### Option Name
`storageState` (JavaScript/Python) | `storageStatePath` (C#/Java)

### Type (JavaScript/Python)
string (path) | Object

### Type (C#/Java)
string (path to file)

### Storage State Object Properties (JavaScript/Python)

#### Cookies Array
- **name** (string) - Required - Cookie name
- **value** (string) - Required - Cookie value
- **domain** (string) - Required - Cookie domain. Prefix with dot for subdomains, e.g., `.example.com`
- **path** (string) - Required - Cookie path
- **expires** (float) - Optional - Unix timestamp in seconds
- **httpOnly** (boolean) - Optional - HTTP-only flag
- **secure** (boolean) - Optional - Secure flag
- **sameSite** (string) - Optional - SameSite attribute value: "Strict", "Lax", or "None"

#### Origins Array
- **origin** (string) - Required - Origin URL
- **localStorage** (Array) - Local storage items
  - **name** (string) - Storage key
  - **value** (string) - Storage value

### Configuration Example (JavaScript/Python)
```json
{
  "storageState": {
    "cookies": [
      {
        "name": "session",
        "value": "abc123",
        "domain": ".example.com",
        "path": "/",
        "expires": 1735689600,
        "httpOnly": true,
        "secure": true,
        "sameSite": "Lax"
      }
    ],
    "origins": [
      {
        "origin": "https://example.com",
        "localStorage": [
          {
            "name": "theme",
            "value": "dark"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Configuration Example (C#/Java)
```json
{
  "storageStatePath": "/path/to/storage-state.json"
}
```
```

