### Reset Authentication for Playwright Tests (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/auth.md

This snippet demonstrates how to explicitly reset the storage state for a specific Playwright test file in JavaScript. By setting `test.use({ storageState: { cookies: [], origins: [] } })`, it clears any pre-configured authentication, allowing tests to run without being logged in. This is useful for testing guest or unauthenticated user flows.

```javascript
import { test } from '@playwright/test';

// Reset storage state for this file to avoid being authenticated
test.use({ storageState: { cookies: [], origins: [] } });

test('not signed in test', async ({ page }) => {
  // ...
});
```

